obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (19112)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19112&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Territorial Waters, Continental`
  line `Shelf, Exclusive Economic Zone and Other Maritime Zones Act, 1976.`
  line
  line `(2) Sections 5 and 7 shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `or on such different dates as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint; and the remaining provisions of this`
  line `Act shall come into force at once.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 15th January, 1977, vide notification No. G.S.R. 16(E), dated 15th January, 1977, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (19113)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19113&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, "limit", in relation to the territorial waters, the continental shelf, the`
  line `exclusive economic zone or any other maritime zone of India, means the limit of such waters, shelf or`
  line `zone with reference to the mainland of India as well as the individual or composite group or groups of`
  line `islands constituting part of the territory of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (19114)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Sovereignty over, and limits of, territorial waters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19114&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The sovereignty of India extends and`
  line `has always extended to the territorial waters of India (hereinafter referred to as the territorial waters) and`
  line `to the seabed and subsoil underlying, and the air space over, such waters.`
  line
  line `(2) The limit of the territorial waters is the line every point of which is at a distance of twelve nautical`
  line `miles from the nearest point of the appropriate baseline.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Central Government may, whenever it`
  line `considers necessary so to do having regard to International Law and State practice, alter, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, the limit of the territorial waters.`
  line
  line `(4) No notification shall be issued under sub-section (3) unless resolutions approving the issue of`
  line `such notification are passed by both Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (19115)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Use of territorial waters by foreign ships.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19115&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the provisions of any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, all foreign ships (other than warships including sub-marines and other`
  line `underwater vehicles) shall enjoy the right of innocent passage through the territorial waters.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, passage is innocent so long as it is not prejudicial to`
  line `the peace, good order or security of India.`
  line
  line `(2) Foreign warships including submarines and other underwater vehicles may enter or pass through`
  line `the territorial waters after giving prior notice to the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that submarines and other underwater vehicles shall navigate on the surface and show their`
  line `flag while passing through such waters.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, if satisfied that it is necessary so to do in the interests of the peace,`
  line `good order or security of India or any part thereof, suspend, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `whether absolutely or subject to such exceptions and qualifications as may be specified in the notification,`
  line `the entry of all or any class of foreign ships into such area of the territorial waters as may be specified in`
  line `the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (19116)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Contiguous zone of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19116&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The contiguous zone of India (hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `contiguous zone) is an area beyond and adjacent to the territorial waters and the limit of the contiguous`
  line `zone is the line every point of which is at a distance of twenty-four nautical miles from the nearest point`
  line `of the baseline referred to in sub-section (2) of section 3.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government may, whenever it`
  line `considers necessary so to do having regard to International Law and State practice, alter, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, the limit of the contiguous zone.`
  line
  line `(3) No notification shall be issued under sub-section (2) unless resolutions approving the issue of`
  line `such notification are passed by both Houses of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may exercise such powers and take such measures in or in relation to the`
  line `contiguous zone as it may consider necessary with respect to,--`
  line
  line `(a) the security of India, and`
  line
  line `(b) immigration, sanitation, customs and other fiscal matters.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) extend with such restrictions and modifications as it thinks fit, any enactment, relating to any`
  line `matter referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (4), for the time being in force in India or`
  line `any part thereof, to the contiguous zone, and`
  line
  line `(b) make such provisions as it may consider necessary in such notification for facilitating the`
  line `enforcement of such enactment,`
  line
  line `and any enactment so extended shall have effect as if the contiguous zone is a part of the territory of`
  line India.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (19117)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Continental shelf.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19117&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The continental shelf of India (hereinafter referred to as the continental`
  line `shelf) comprises the seabed and subsoil of the submarine areas that extend beyond the limit of its`
  line `territorial waters throughout the natural prolongation of its land territory to the outer edge of the`
  line `continental margin or to a distance of two hundred nautical miles from the baseline referred to in subsection`
  line `(2) of section 3 where the outer edge of the continental margin does not extend up to that distance.`
  line
  line `(2) India has, and always had, full and exclusive sovereign rights in respect of its continental shelf.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (2), the Union has in the`
  line `continental shelf,--`
  line
  line `(a) sovereign rights for the purposes of exploration, exploitation, conservation and management`
  line
  line `of all resources;`
  line
  line `(b) exclusive rights and jurisdiction for the construction, maintenance or operation of artificial`
  line `islands, off-shore terminals, installations and other structures and devices necessary for the`
  line `exploration and exploitation of the resources of the continental shelf or for the convenience of`
  line `shipping or for any other purpose;`
  line
  line `(c) exclusive jurisdiction to authorise, regulate and control scientific research; and`
  line
  line `(d) exclusive jurisdiction to preserve and protect the marine environment and to prevent and`
  line `control marine pollution.`
  line
  line `(4) No person (including a foreign Government) shall, except under, and in accordance with, the`
  line `terms of a licence or a letter of authority granted by the Central Government, explore the continental shelf`
  line `or exploit its resources or carry out any search or excavation or conduct any research within the`
  line `continental shelf or drill therein or construct, maintain or operate any artificial island, off-shore terminal,`
  line `installation or other structure or device therein for any purpose whatsoever.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) declare any area of the continental shelf and its superjacent waters to be a designated area; and`
  line
  line `(b) make such provisions as it may deem necessary with respect to,--`
  line
  line `(i) the exploration, exploitation and protection of the resources of the continental shelf within`
  line `such designated area; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the safety and protection of artificial islands, off-shore terminals, installations and other`
  line `structures and devices in such designated area; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the protection of marine environment of such designated area; or`
  line
  line `(iv) customs and other fiscal matters in relation to such designated area.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--A notification issued under this sub-section may provide for the regulation of entry`
  line `into and passage through the designated area of foreign ships by the establishment of fairways, sealanes,`
  line `traffic separation schemes or any other mode of ensuring freedom of navigation which is not prejudicial`
  line `to the interests of India.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) extend with such restrictions and modifications as it thinks fit, any enactment for the time`
  line `being in force in India or any part thereof to the continental shelf or any part [including any`
  line `designated area under sub-section (5)] thereof; and`
  line
  line `(b) make such provisions as it may consider necessary for facilitating the enforcement of such`
  line enactment,
  line
  line `and any enactment so extended shall have effect as if the continental shelf or the part [including, as the`
  line `case may be, any designated area under sub-section (5)] thereof to which it has been extended is a part of`
  line `the territory of India.`
  line
  line `(7) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (2) and subject to any measures that may be`
  line `necessary for protecting the interests of India, the Central Government may not impede the laying or`
  line `maintenance of submarine cables or pipelines on the continental shelf by foreign States:`
  line
  line `Provided that the consent of the Central Government shall be necessary for the delineation of the`
  line `course for the laying of such cables or pipelines.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (19118)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Exclusive economic zone.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19118&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The exclusive economic zone of India (hereinafter referred to as`
  line `the exclusive economic zone) is an area beyond and adjacent to the territorial waters, and the limit of such`
  line `zone is two hundred nautical miles from the baseline referred to in sub-section (2) of section 3.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government may, whenever it`
  line `considers necessary so to do having regard to International Law and State practice, alter, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, the Limit of the exclusive economic zone.`
  line
  line `(3) No notification shall be issued under sub-section (2) unless resolutions approving the issue of`
  line `such notification are passed by both Houses of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(4) In the exclusive economic zone, the Union has,--`
  line
  line `(a) sovereign rights for the purpose of exploration, exploitation, conservation and management of`
  line `the natural resources, both living and non-living as well as for producing energy from tides, winds`
  line `and currents;`
  line
  line `(b) exclusive rights and jurisdiction for the construction, maintenance or operation of artificial`
  line `islands, off-shore terminals, installations and other structures and devices necessary for the`
  line `exploration and exploitation of the resources of the zone or for the convenience of shipping or for any`
  line `other purpose;`
  line
  line `(c) exclusive jurisdiction to authorise, regulate and control scientific research;`
  line
  line `(d) exclusive jurisdiction to preserve and protect the marine environment and to prevent and`
  line `control marine pollution; and`
  line
  line `(e) such other rights as are recognised by International Law.`
  line
  line `(5) No person (including a foreign Government) shall, except under, and in accordance with, the`
  line `terms of any agreement with the Central Government or of a licence or a letter of authority granted by the`
  line `Central Government, explore or exploit any resources of the exclusive economic zone or carry out any`
  line `search or excavation or conduct any research within the exclusive economic zone or drill therein or`
  line `construct, maintain or operate any artificial island, off-shore terminal, installation or other structure or`
  line `device therein for any purpose whatsoever:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply in relation to fishing by a citizen of India.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) declare any area of the exclusive economic zone to be a designated area; and`
  line
  line `(b) make such provisions as it may deem necessary with respect to,--`
  line
  line `(i) the exploration, exploitation and protection of the resources of such designated area; or`
  line
  line `(ii) other activities for the economic exploitation and exploration of such designated area such`
  line `as the production of energy from tides, winds and currents; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the safety and protection of artificial islands, off-shore terminals, installations and other`
  line `structures and devices in such designated area; or`
  line
  line `(iv) the protection of marine environment of such designated area; or`
  line
  line `(v) customs and other fiscal matters in relation to such designated area.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--A notification issued under this sub-section may provide for the regulation of entry`
  line `into and passage through the designated area of foreign ships by the establishment of fairways, sealanes,`
  line
  line `traffic separation schemes or any other mode of ensuring freedom of navigation which is not prejudicial`
  line `to the interests of India.`
  line
  line `(7) The Central Government may, by notification in the official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) extend, with such restrictions and modifications as it thinks fit, any enactment for the time`
  line `being in force in India or any part thereof to the exclusive economic zone or any part thereof; and`
  line
  line `(b) make such provisions as it may consider necessary for facilitating the enforcement of such`
  line enactment,
  line
  line `and any enactment so extended shall have effect as if the exclusive economic zone or the part thereof to`
  line `which it has been extended is a part of the territory of India.`
  line
  line `(8) The provisions of sub-section (7) of section 6 shall apply in relation to the laying or maintenance`
  line `of submarine cables or pipelines on the seabed of the exclusive economic zone as they apply in relation to`
  line `the laying or maintenance of submarine cables or pipelines on the seabed of the continental shelf.`
  line
  line `(9) In the exclusive economic zone and the air space over the zone, ships and aircraft of all States`
  line `shall, subject to the exercise by India of its rights within the zone, enjoy freedom of navigation and over`
  line flight.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (19119)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Historic waters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19119&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify the limits of such waters adjacent to its land territory as are the historic waters of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The sovereignty of India extends, and has always extended, to the historic waters of India and to`
  line `the seabed and subsoil underlying, and the air space over, such waters.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (19120)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Maritime boundaries between India and States having coasts opposite or adjacent to those of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19120&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The maritime boundaries between India and any State whose coast is opposite or adjacent to`
  line `that of India in regard to their respective territorial waters, contiguous zones, continental shelves, exclusive economic zones and other maritime zones shall be as determined by agreement (whether`
  line `entered into before or after the commencement of this section) between India and such State and pending`
  line `such agreement between India and any such State, and unless any other provisional arrangements are`
  line `agreed to between them, the maritime boundaries between India and such State shall not extend beyond`
  line `the line every point of which is equidistant from the nearest point from which the breadth of the territorial`
  line `waters of India and of such State are measured.`
  line
  line `(2) Every agreement referred to in sub-section (1) shall, as soon as may be after it is entered into, be`
  line `published in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall have effect notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `other provision of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (19121)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Publication of charts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19121&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may cause the baseline referred to in subsection`
  line `(2) of section 3, the limits of the territorial waters, the contiguous zone, the continental shelf, the`
  line `exclusive economic zone and the historic waters of India and the maritime boundaries as settled by`
  line `agreements referred to in section 9 to be published in charts.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (19122)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Offences.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19122&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes any provision of this Act or of any notification thereunder shall`
  line `(without prejudice to any other action which may be taken against such person under any other provision`
  line `of this or of any other enactment) be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three years, or`
  line `with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (19123)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19123&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act or the rules made thereunder has`
  line `been committed by a company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of,`
  line `and was responsible to the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the`
  line `company shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) where an offence under this Act or the`
  line `rules made thereunder has been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been`
  line `committed with the consent or the connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any`
  line `director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (19124)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Place of trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19124&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Any person committing an offence under this Act or any rules made thereunder`
  line `or under any of the enactments extended under this Act or under the rules made thereunder may be tried`
  line `for the offence in any place in which he may be found or in such other place as the Central Government`
  line `may, by general or special order, published in the Official Gazette, direct in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (19125)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Previous sanction of the Central Government for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19125&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution shall be`
  line `instituted against any person in respect of any offence under this Act or the rules made thereunder without`
  line `the previous sanction of the Central Government or such officer or authority as may be authorised by that`
  line `Government by order in writing in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (19126)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19126&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) regulation of the conduct of any person in the territorial waters, the contiguous zone, the`
  line `continental shelf, the exclusive economic zone or any other maritime zone of India;`
  line
  line `(b) regulation of the exploration and exploitation, conservation and management of the resources`
  line `of the continental shelf;`
  line
  line `(c) regulation of the exploration, exploitation, conservation and management of the resources of`
  line `the exclusive economic zone;`
  line
  line `(d) regulation of the construction, maintenance and operation of artificial islands, off-shore`
  line `terminals, installations and other structures and devices referred to in sections 6 and 7;`
  line
  line `(e) preservation and protection of the marine environment and prevention and control of marine`
  line `pollution for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) authorisation, regulation and control of the conduct of scientific research for the purposes of`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) fees in relation to licences and letters of authority referred to in sub-section (4) of section 6`
  line `and sub-section (5) of section 7 or for any other purpose; or`
  line
  line `(h) any matter incidental to any of the matters specified in clauses (a) to (g).`
  line
  line `(3) In making any rule under this section, the Central Government may provide that a contravention`
  line `thereof shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three years, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to any amount, or with both.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule made under this Act and every notification issued under sub-section (5) of section 6 or`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 7 shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made or issued, before each House`
  line `of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or in two or more successive sessions and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `the notification or both Houses agree that the rule or notification should not be issued, the rule or`
  line `notification shall, thereafter, have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may`
  line `be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule or notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (19127)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Removal of difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455&sectionId=19127&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_10_10_00002_197680_1517807318455
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act`
  line `or of any of the enactments extended under this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in`
  line `the Official Gazette, make such provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act or, as the case`
  line `may be, of such enactment, as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of any difficulty arising in giving effect to any provision of this Act, after the`
  line `expiry of three years from the commencement of such provision;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any difficulty arising in giving effect to the provisions of any enactment`
  line `extended under this Act, after the expiry of three years from the extension of such enactment.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
